2011-10-03T05:17:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/france-daybook-vivendi-ceo-speaks-areva-eramet-edf-renault.html
Vivendi SA Chief Executive Officer
Jean-Bernard Levy appears at the European Telecommunications
Network Operators’ Association conference in Brussels, along
with other industry CEOs.  The French government is studying possible ways of
allowing Areva SA to sell its 26 percent stake in Eramet SA,
daily La Tribune reported, without citing anyone.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Vivendi CEO Jean-Bernard Levy at ETNO conference in Brussels,
11 a.m.  EARNINGS
*No major earnings scheduled.  ECONOMY:  Data and events today
* 09:50 PMI Manufacturing (Sept.)  GOVERNMENT:
*Industry minister Eric Besson meets with the National Digital
Council. 08:30.
*Ministers meet to open commission on the future of Paris’ Orly
airport. 09:00.
*Budget Minister  Francois Baroin  meets with Eurogroup finance
ministers in  Luxembourg . Afternoon.  EQUITIES:
* Accor SA (AC)  : The hotel manager said it signed a franchise
agreement with Jupiter Hotels, bringing its U.K. network to 300
hotels. The shares fell 2 percent to 20.15 euros.
*EADS NV (EAD FP): Airlines operating the Airbus owner’s A380
superjumbo may be required to modify equipment that connects
the plane’s engines to its wings to reduce the risk of fire,
safety regulators said. The shares fell 1.8 percent to 21.2
euros.
* EDF SA (EDF)  : Italian shareholders of Edison SpA are ready
to cede control to EDF,  France ’s largest utility, in exchange
for an option to sell their stake and the breakup of unit
Edipower, according to two people familiar with the situation.
The shares fell 1.5 percent to 21.81 euros.
* Renault SA (RNO)  : The car manufacturer won a contract to
supply the French state and state-owned postal service with
more than 15,000 electric cars, Le Figaro reported without
saying how it obtained the information. The shares fell 3.6
percent to 25.07 euros.  MARKETS:
*The benchmark CAC 40 Index fell 1.5 percent to 2,981.96.
*The SBF120 Index decreased 1.6 percent to 2,280.30.  INTERVIEWS ELSEWHERE:
-07:15 BFM: Steria CEO Francois Enaud
-07:45  Canal Plus : Ecology Minister Nathalie Kosciusko-Morizet
-08:15 France Info: Socialist presidential candidate Francois
Hollande
-08:20 France Inter: Transport Minister Thierry Mariani
